commit.message: Re #149 Add underlining colours and styles

Re #149 Introduce possiblity of parameter substrings

Under 13.1.8 of T.416 (03/93), certain SGR parameter values can be followed by a parameter substring (also known as subparameters). T.416 used them for SGR parameter values 38 and 48, but they have also been put to use in the case of fancy and coloured underlining.
Fix linker error about a duplicate symbol

Fix #160 Add `hNowSupportsANSI`

Also, in Windows Terminal and ConHost terminals, `hSupportsANSI` will yield `False` if the the processing of \'ANSI\' control characters in output is not enabled.

Also makes deprecated `hSupportsANSIWithoutEmulation` consistent with `hNowSupportsANSI`.
Drop support for legacy Windows requiring emulation
Changes consequent on dropping support for GHC before GHC 7.10.1

Update cabal-version of ansi-terminal.cabal to 1.22

The Cabal file now uses a reexported-modules field.
Change lower bound on base for ansi-terminal-types

Re #151 Step 3 Depend on ansi-terminal-types

Also drops support for GHC versions before GHC 7.10.1, because those versions of GHC did not support re-exported modules.
Update CI for unsupported GHC versions
Re #151 Step 1 - Move ansi-terminal package to its own folder
